BNY Mellon is a global financial services company focused on helping clients manage and service their financial assets, operating in 36 countries and serving more than 100 markets. BNY Mellon is a leading provider of financial services to institutions, corporations and high-net-worth individuals, providing superior asset management and wealth management, asset servicing, issuer services, clearing services and treasury services through a worldwide client-focused team.
Team Description: (Overview of the team)

This role is within the Office of Regulatory Relations (ORR). BNY Mellons ORR provides centralized management of BNY Mellons relationship with prudential regulators. The primary functions of the group include, but are not limited to: developing and managing protocols and processes for engaging regulators; acting as a central clearinghouse for regulatory requests; exam management; assisting regulators to navigate and understand BNY Mellon; and supporting the monitoring and tracking of regulator interactions, including imbedding lessons learned processes. The ORR also plays a critical to ensure that BNY Mellon delivers a consistent and connected enterprise wide message to the Regulators. The group is also responsible for facilitating the development and enhancement of long-term relationships with key regulators. The team also plays a vital function involving regular briefings with BNY Mellon senior executives on the regulatory agenda.
Job Purpose:
The position of ORR Assistant Exam/Process Manager will be responsible to develop and manage project plans and assignment/approval matrix in support of all regulatory interaction; tracks progress and follows up with stakeholders on deliverables; serves as the scribe for all meetings; and coordinates the submission of any materials to the regulators.
Responsibilities:
The position involves supporting the Regulatory Relationship Manager in:

The planning and coordination activities of regulatory examinations, e.g., responses to First Day Letters, development of regulatory presentation materials, etc.
Development of project plans to ensure each phase of the exam lifecycle is well planned and executed
Assist in the scheduling and coordination of all regulatory meetings including review and challenge sessions/dry-runs
Produce exam meeting minutes and list of key action items following each meeting
Strong project management skills with the ability to juggle competing priorities
Ability to hold/facilitate planning meetings to talk through requests to ensure appropriate subject matter experts are assigned to address the regulatory request
Produce MI of regulatory deliverables/commitment.
Qualifications
The successful candidate will have at least 5-7 years relevant work experience in roles within the financial services industry, preferably, which have involved interaction with regulators. Other required experience includes:
Bachelor degree
Understanding of the financial services & banking industry
Strong project management skills
Intellectual curiosity
Effective communicators with strong relationship management skills

