For over 230 years, Bank of New York Mellon (BNY Mellon) has been at the center of the global financial markets, providing the worlds leading institutions the tools, capabilities, and services to be distinctive investors. BNY Mellon has approximately $15 billion in revenues and market capitalization of approximately $50 billion.
 
BNY Mellon is a leader in the world of investment services and investment management, and our businesses support the full range of stakeholders of the financial system including:


Managing the custody of over $31 trillion financial assets of the worlds leading institutional investors, hedge funds, sovereign wealth funds, and corporates
Investing over $1.8 trillion as one of the largest global asset managers across a wide range of asset classes
Providing collateral, liquidity, and funding for the worlds largest banks through our markets franchise
Serving family offices and high net worth individuals in our top 10 wealth manager ($250 billion assets)
